06:35.666 --> 06:37.496
You got a piece for protection?

06:37.583 --> 06:41.253
Yeah, I got a piece for protection.
Got a side piece.

06:41.333 --> 06:44.083
I got Smith on one side
and Wesson on the other.

06:44.166 --> 06:45.326
[all laugh]

06:50.458 --> 06:53.538
-Money, please.
-No. You gotta go. You gotta go, son.

06:53.625 --> 06:54.825
-I'm good.
-Man.

06:55.416 --> 06:57.166
-GI, GI.
-They don't have no age limit

06:57.250 --> 06:58.670
-on a bar in Vietnam, then?
-GI, GI.

06:58.750 --> 07:01.460
No, no, you gotta... Come on,
get him the fuck out of here.

07:04.541 --> 07:07.171
Money, money. GI.

07:07.666 --> 07:09.576
-There you go, all right.
-Twenty bucks.

07:09.666 --> 07:10.496
Go.

07:10.583 --> 07:13.383
Now he got more in his damn cup
than I got in my wallet.

07:13.458 --> 07:15.248
-[chuckles] Man, they'll take you.
-Shit.

07:16.458 --> 07:17.458
It's a damn shame.

07:21.166 --> 07:22.326
On the real, man.

07:24.958 --> 07:27.328
We got back from Nam, we didn't get
nothing but a hard damn time.

07:27.416 --> 07:29.496
-Folks called us baby killers.
-Yeah.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.463
See, I bought into all that bullshit.

07:31.541 --> 07:33.671
How did your life change? Yeah, right.

07:34.875 --> 07:38.625
Time we got these free-loading immigrants
off our backs and build that wall.

07:39.625 --> 07:42.375
Negroes better wake the fuck up
with the quickness, man.

07:42.458 --> 07:44.958
-No, no, no, no, no!
-I'm just saying. I'm--

07:45.041 --> 07:48.751
Don't tell me that you voted
for President Fake Bone Spurs.

07:48.833 --> 07:51.173
-Yeah, I voted for him.
-Get the fuck out of here.

07:51.250 --> 07:52.830
-[scoffing chuckle]
-He didn't vote for him.

07:52.916 --> 07:54.576
-I thought that was you.
-Impeach him.

07:54.666 --> 07:59.166
That grinnin'-ass Negro on the front row.
Ta-ta-ta-da!

07:59.250 --> 08:02.920
Right there behind Trump at that rally.
"Ha! Ha! It's me! It's me!"

08:03.000 --> 08:04.710
[crowd cheering]

08:04.791 --> 08:06.541
Blacks for Trump, you watch.

08:07.291 --> 08:11.251
You watch.
Those signs are great, thank you.

08:12.041 --> 08:13.131
Fake news.

08:13.208 --> 08:15.578
Uh-huh. See? That's what they all go to.

08:15.666 --> 08:17.036
-Fake news.
-Always go to that one.

08:17.125 --> 08:19.165
-Yeah.
-I'm tired of not getting mine, man.

08:19.250 --> 08:21.080
I feel you. I feel you.

08:21.875 --> 08:25.955
Been fucked my whole goddamn life, bruh.
Goin' for me!

08:26.041 --> 08:27.421
Shit. For real.

08:27.875 --> 08:29.995
-Huh.
-I mean, back in the day,

08:30.291 --> 08:32.711
-being a brother meant something.
-Yeah, man.

08:32.791 --> 08:34.131
We fought against the man.

08:34.207 --> 08:35.878
-We loved one another.
-Amen.

08:35.957 --> 08:39.168
We became ace boon coon blood brothers
out there in that damn jungle.

08:39.250 --> 08:40.080
-Preach on it.
-Yeah.

08:40.166 --> 08:42.206
-Stormin' Norm demanded it.
-He did.

08:42.291 --> 08:43.501
-Sure did.
-All right, come on.

08:43.582 --> 08:45.333
-Yeah.
-Here we go. Boom!

08:45.416 --> 08:46.826
-[all] Boom!
-All right, yeah.

08:53.125 --> 08:55.035
-Otis.
-Vinh.

08:55.625 --> 08:59.035
-This is our guide, Vinh.
-Hey, I'm Eddie.

08:59.625 --> 09:02.245
-Vinh.
-I'm Melvin, man.

09:02.333 --> 09:03.673
-Nice to meet you.
-How you doing?

09:03.750 --> 09:05.080
-[Vinh] Good.
-Paul, man.

09:05.166 --> 09:06.166
-Good to meet you.
-Yeah.

09:06.250 --> 09:09.380
Gentlemen, welcome back to Vietnam.

09:09.958 --> 09:11.418
-Thank you.
-[Melvin] Thank you, man.

09:14.625 --> 09:17.705
I have itinerary for you.
That's for you.

09:18.250 --> 09:19.540
-For you.
-[Otis] Thank you.

09:19.625 --> 09:21.455
-For you. Thank you.
-Pull up a seat.

09:23.583 --> 09:28.463
I still think hiking into the jungle
without me as your guide is a big mistake.

09:28.875 --> 09:31.375
-We know that jungle, man.
-Yes, we sure do.

09:31.458 --> 09:32.788
-Oh, yeah.
-[low chuckles]

09:33.625 --> 09:35.625
[Vinh] Do you have
the necessary documents?

09:35.708 --> 09:37.038
[Otis] Yes, there you go.

09:39.166 --> 09:43.246
From the Pentagon...
and from the Vietnamese government.

09:44.500 --> 09:46.580
When we locate Norman's remains,

09:46.666 --> 09:49.956
the DPAA is gonna send in a recovery team
to bring him back home.

09:50.041 --> 09:51.881
Arlington National Cemetery.

09:53.875 --> 09:57.575
Hey, man, what the... what the fuck
are they staring at, man?

09:57.666 --> 09:58.576
Who?

09:58.666 --> 10:00.456
Those two right there.

10:01.541 --> 10:05.751
Shit. Those two over there, they've been
staring at us for the last ten minutes.

10:05.833 --> 10:06.883
[speaking Vietnamese]

10:06.958 --> 10:10.668
-[Eddie] Just chill, man. Just chill.
-Chill? People staring at me, man.

10:10.750 --> 10:11.830
Staring at all of us.

10:12.416 --> 10:14.666
Those gentlemen just buy you this drink.

10:14.750 --> 10:18.670
They are former Viet Cong and wanna
welcome you all back to their country.

10:18.750 --> 10:19.580
Yeah?

10:20.541 --> 10:23.581
-[Vinh] One of them is my cousin, Nguyen.
-[Otis] Get outta here.

10:23.666 --> 10:25.536
And my father's younger brother.

10:26.833 --> 10:29.793
-[Eddie] But you're from the south.
-They fought for the north.

10:30.458 --> 10:32.828
Nguyen does tours
for North Vietnamese tourists.

10:35.208 --> 10:39.168
The American War turned Vietnamese family
against Vietnamese family.

10:42.916 --> 10:44.916
-Paul.
-Hey, man.

10:45.500 --> 10:48.670
Those could've been the dudes
that zapped Norm, that's all I'm saying.

10:48.750 --> 10:54.500
Will you raise your goddamn glass?
The American War is over. Come on.

10:56.416 --> 10:57.286
Come on, man.

11:02.708 --> 11:03.878
[in Vietnamese]

11:06.916 --> 11:08.076
[Otis] Whoo!

11:09.250 --> 11:12.790
-[in English] Good night.
-Oh, yeah. Oh.

11:14.583 --> 11:17.083
-Feelin' the love.
-Oh, man. Look at him.

11:17.166 --> 11:18.416
-I tell ya.
-I know.

11:18.500 --> 11:19.420
[all chuckling]

11:21.916 --> 11:23.826
[laughing and mocking in Vietnamese]

11:23.916 --> 11:25.996
GI! GI! [laughing]

11:26.916 --> 11:28.916
[dramatic instrumental music plays]

11:53.791 --> 11:56.671
Now I know why this mission
was so damn important.

11:57.750 --> 11:59.830
It's about what this war is all about.

12:01.083 --> 12:02.253
There it is.

12:36.166 --> 12:40.626
[Norman] All right, Bloods.
Our objective is in the C-47.

13:05.791 --> 13:07.671
[soldiers speaking Vietnamese]

13:19.791 --> 13:20.631
[groans]

13:28.541 --> 13:30.211
[soldiers yelling in Vietnamese]

13:35.583 --> 13:38.423
-[Norman] Hold yourself! Hold on!
-[all shouting]

13:43.708 --> 13:45.578
[all screaming]

13:46.958 --> 13:48.128
-Come on.
-[Melvin] Hold on!

13:56.625 --> 13:57.785
[all shouting]

13:57.875 --> 13:59.875
-[Eddie] Lock it up!
-[Norman] Cover the Bloods to the plane!

13:59.958 --> 14:02.288
-[Paul] Go! Go, man! You got it!
-Harlow and Cots, KIA!

14:03.500 --> 14:06.290
-[soldiers scream]
-[firing continues]

14:17.208 --> 14:18.038
[soldier screams]

14:18.791 --> 14:20.581
[Norman] Lay down cover fire!

14:22.583 --> 14:23.793
[Otis] Go!

14:32.708 --> 14:33.538
Reloading.

14:46.500 --> 14:47.960
-Reload!
-Reloading.

14:49.625 --> 14:50.745
[soldiers scream]

14:59.833 --> 15:01.003
Move out! Move out!

15:11.625 --> 15:12.995
[speaking Vietnamese]

15:15.416 --> 15:16.706
Fuck! Jammed!

15:20.208 --> 15:22.458
[Otis] Come on! Go!

15:23.083 --> 15:24.333
Move, move, move!

15:26.083 --> 15:27.043
[speaking Vietnamese]

15:34.208 --> 15:35.458
[Norman] Go, go, go!

15:38.333 --> 15:39.253
Go!

15:42.333 --> 15:44.173
Man down! Man down!

15:52.166 --> 15:52.996
[groans]

15:53.291 --> 15:55.171
[soldiers yelling in Vietnamese]

15:58.041 --> 16:00.461
[Norman] Check fire. Paul! Get up! Get up!

16:04.500 --> 16:06.130
[soldiers yelling in Vietnamese]

16:13.875 --> 16:15.285
Team one, take security!

16:16.333 --> 16:17.633
[Paul] Set security!

16:19.375 --> 16:20.575
Set security!

16:31.041 --> 16:32.541
Hey, Paul, come inside!

16:38.916 --> 16:39.746
Clear!

16:45.041 --> 16:46.041
Bloods!

16:48.333 --> 16:49.583
[Paul] Yo, come on in here.

17:03.291 --> 17:05.290
All right. Let's see what we got here.

17:12.250 --> 17:14.380
-[Melvin] Out of sight!
-[Paul] Great googly-moogly.

17:14.458 --> 17:15.708
You know what this means?

17:16.500 --> 17:18.000
We gold standard.

17:18.375 --> 17:19.375
[laughs]

17:19.750 --> 17:20.960
We gold standard.

17:23.290 --> 17:26.790
I've run many tours for GIs
from the American War.

17:28.833 --> 17:31.503
Glad you can now see our country
in a different light.

17:33.375 --> 17:37.495
Wow! Will you look at this?

17:37.583 --> 17:40.133
-[Melvin] It's a whole different place.
-I can't believe it.

17:40.208 --> 17:43.128
They didn't need us.
They should've just sent Mickey D's,

17:43.208 --> 17:44.668
Pizza Hut and The Colonel,

17:44.750 --> 17:46.960
and we would have defeated the V.C.
in one week.

17:47.041 --> 17:48.881
-You got it. [chuckles]
-Finger-lickin' good.

17:50.000 --> 17:51.330
Paul, when did you serve?

17:52.458 --> 17:58.458
I did three tours, man.
'67 to '71. 1st Infantry.

17:59.166 --> 18:01.916
Were you involved
in Operation Junction City?

18:02.000 --> 18:04.170
-We were there. We were all there.
-Oh, yeah.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.080
Yeah.

18:05.875 --> 18:07.165
My father was there, too.

18:07.875 --> 18:10.825
-Yeah?
-25th Infantry, ARVN.

18:12.041 --> 18:13.751
He fought to the very last man.

18:14.250 --> 18:16.920
My brother, give it to me. Give it to me.

18:18.916 --> 18:21.626
My family was here in Saigon when it fell.

18:21.708 --> 18:25.668
My dad spent 18 months
in a communist re-education camp.

18:25.750 --> 18:26.580
Wow.

18:27.166 --> 18:28.826
Many other were not so lucky.

18:30.666 --> 18:33.706
Hey, y'all remember
those fugazi  Rambo  movies?

18:33.791 --> 18:34.921
-Sly.
-Yeah.

18:35.000 --> 18:36.580
I like them shits, man.

18:36.666 --> 18:38.536
You gotta be fucking kidding me, man.

18:38.625 --> 18:42.455
Him and that... that dude, uh,
Walker, Texas Ranger.

18:42.541 --> 18:44.251
-I ain't saying nothing about him.
-Man!

18:44.333 --> 18:47.923
Out there trying to save
some imaginary POWs.

18:48.000 --> 18:51.880
All them Holly-weird motherfuckers
trying to go back and win the Vietnam War.

18:51.958 --> 18:56.708
Yeah. I would be the first cat in line
if there was a flick about a real hero,

18:56.791 --> 18:59.881
you know, one of our blood.
Somebody like Milton Olive.

18:59.958 --> 19:03.288
[Eddie]  That man jumped on that grenade
and saved his Bloods' lives.

19:03.375 --> 19:07.245
[Otis]  And he was the first brother
to be awarded the Medal of Honor in Nam.

19:07.333 --> 19:08.633
Eighteen years old.

19:08.708 --> 19:13.168
Look, I love y'all and all that bullshit,
but, uh, I ain't doin' that.

19:13.250 --> 19:15.500
Man, nobody want you to die for them.

19:15.583 --> 19:16.793
'Cause I ain't.

19:17.291 --> 19:19.711
Like Aretha sang, "You better think."

19:19.791 --> 19:21.751
-Oh, Vinh.
-What the fuck he talkin' about?

19:21.833 --> 19:25.503
Listen, Bloods, I'm out, all right?
Thank you very much.

19:25.583 --> 19:26.713
-Thank you.
-All right.

19:26.791 --> 19:29.461
-Oh. Oh, oh. Be careful, man.
-Yeah?

19:30.291 --> 19:32.421
I'll be careful. Later.

19:32.958 --> 19:34.078
Where's he going?

19:34.958 --> 19:37.038
[Paul]  He got something
to take care of, man.

19:47.291 --> 19:48.831
[footsteps approaching]

19:56.875 --> 19:57.875
Tiên...

20:00.041 --> 20:01.631
you have hardly changed.

20:01.708 --> 20:07.288
We both know that's not true.
But thank you for being so kind.

20:11.958 --> 20:13.828
You look like
you've done well for yourself.

20:14.416 --> 20:15.826
We find a way.

20:17.250 --> 20:21.540
-Yes, we do. When we can.
-Yes.

20:22.250 --> 20:24.170
[in Vietnamese]

20:26.291 --> 20:27.501
[Otis chuckles]

20:28.875 --> 20:30.955
[in English] The gold is belong
to Vietnamese government.

20:31.916 --> 20:35.166
Monsieur Desroche converts the gold
into cash.

20:36.125 --> 20:40.375
He's the only person that I know
who can handle a transaction of this size.

20:42.333 --> 20:45.083
-Have you dealt with him before?
-Yes.

20:46.083 --> 20:48.963
He's expensive. 20%.

20:50.083 --> 20:52.213
-[sighs]
-And I will need 10%.

20:52.291 --> 20:54.631
And there's no other way to move this?

20:55.458 --> 20:56.288
[door opens]

20:56.375 --> 20:59.165
-International export is my business.
-[door closes]

20:59.250 --> 21:01.790
-It's why you call me.
-Yeah.

21:02.666 --> 21:04.376
[woman in Vietnamese]

21:13.041 --> 21:16.251
[in English] This is my daughter, Michon.

21:18.583 --> 21:23.383
And this is my old friend Otis.
From American War.

21:24.250 --> 21:26.380
-[Otis whispers] It's, uh...
-Hello, Otis.

21:28.875 --> 21:30.375
It's very nice to meet you.

21:31.083 --> 21:32.383
[in Vietnamese]

21:33.000 --> 21:34.330
[in English] Thanks, my dear.

21:53.541 --> 21:54.541
[sighs]

22:13.916 --> 22:14.876
Is, uh...

22:20.166 --> 22:25.206
Is, uh... Is that our daughter? Our...

22:26.250 --> 22:28.330
Yes, she is.

22:31.166 --> 22:34.536
She was a bastard child of the enemy.

22:36.625 --> 22:38.205
I was a whore.

22:38.791 --> 22:42.541
Her father was a  moi,  the nigger.

22:45.333 --> 22:47.923
The white GI taught us that word.

22:48.833 --> 22:50.463
Everyone want us out.

22:51.583 --> 22:55.503
We was too dirty to even clean the toilet.

22:57.791 --> 23:01.501
They call our beautiful Michon
the cockroach.

23:07.208 --> 23:09.168
-Mmm?
-No.

23:19.458 --> 23:20.748
Good night, Tiên.

23:20.833 --> 23:22.423
Good night, Otis.

23:27.708 --> 23:29.288
[Michon in Vietnamese]

24:12.916 --> 24:14.376
[bell tolling]

24:24.125 --> 24:27.285
[in English] May I ask, how did they
end up in your possession?

24:27.375 --> 24:29.745
You ask a lotta goddamn questions,
wringer.

24:32.166 --> 24:36.326
Monsieur, maybe they're from a bank
you just knocked off in Manila.

24:36.416 --> 24:39.126
Or maybe the authorities
are looking for them.

24:39.208 --> 24:41.128
I don't need that kind of shit.

24:41.208 --> 24:43.578
We ain't no international criminals,
you dig?

24:43.666 --> 24:47.376
In my line of work,
I have to be very careful,

24:47.458 --> 24:51.458
and that means knowing exactly
who I am in business with.

24:51.541 --> 24:53.961
This cat getting on
my last goddamn nerve, man.

24:54.541 --> 24:57.211
Gentlemen, I believe
our business is finished.

24:57.291 --> 24:58.461
[Paul] Hey, wait a minute.

24:59.250 --> 25:02.080
Do me a favor. Sit down, please?
Just give us that respect.

25:04.000 --> 25:06.040
Where were Frenchies in World War II?

25:07.875 --> 25:10.075
Hitler had y'all by the snails.

25:11.083 --> 25:14.173
The goddamn US of A saved your asses.

25:14.250 --> 25:16.960
If it wasn't for good ol' Uncle Sam,
all of yous,

25:17.041 --> 25:20.751
y'all be speaking the  deutsche
eating bratwurst,

25:20.833 --> 25:26.543
schnitzels and sauerkraut instead
of croissants, snails and escargot.

25:26.625 --> 25:27.785
Come on, Blood. Let it go.

25:27.875 --> 25:29.455
-No, man, no.
-Just let it go!

25:29.541 --> 25:32.171
No, fuck that. I ain't done.

25:34.750 --> 25:37.500
This motherfucker can't tell me shit.

25:38.208 --> 25:40.748
My daddy, God rest his soul,

25:40.833 --> 25:45.043
landed in Normandy and killed  beaucoup
goose-stepping Nazis.

25:45.125 --> 25:49.535
Let me tell you something, them Nazis
weren't no punks neither. Not like you.

25:54.291 --> 25:56.881
-Yeah, okay, I'm done.
-You feel better?

25:56.958 --> 25:58.418
-Yeah.
-[Desroche] Well,

25:59.000 --> 26:04.670
I thank you for this ignorant American
one-sided version of World War II.

26:04.750 --> 26:08.580
Please understand. He taking big risk.

26:08.666 --> 26:09.916
And we ain't?

26:11.041 --> 26:15.251
DaRoach, we gotta trust you,
and you gotta trust us.

26:17.166 --> 26:18.416
[Otis] Mr. Desroche...

26:20.666 --> 26:24.376
Our platoon was ordered
to find a C-47 CIA plane

26:24.458 --> 26:28.168
that went down with a payroll
for the native people. The Lahu.

26:28.250 --> 26:30.960
Now, they didn't wanna be paid
in paper currency,

26:31.041 --> 26:35.251
so Uncle Sam was paying them in gold bars
for their help against the V.C.

26:35.958 --> 26:38.208
Well, we found the gold, and we...

26:38.291 --> 26:43.131
We bury it. For now.
They ask, we say the V.C. got it.

26:43.958 --> 26:46.788
Later on, we come back and collect.

26:46.875 --> 26:48.205
You mean rip it off.

26:48.291 --> 26:50.001
We ain't ripping off shit!

26:51.250 --> 26:53.420
Who feel like
they're ripping something off?

26:54.416 --> 26:57.706
We was the very first people
that died for this red, white and blue.

26:58.666 --> 26:59.826
Yeah, that's right.

27:00.708 --> 27:04.878
It was a soul brother, Crispus Attucks
at the motherfuckin' Boston Massacre.

27:05.708 --> 27:08.458
We been dying for this country
from the very get,

27:08.541 --> 27:11.041
hoping one day they'd give us
our rightful place.

27:11.125 --> 27:14.415
All they give us was a foot
up our black asses. Well, fuck that.

27:15.125 --> 27:19.995
I say the USA owe us. We built this bitch!

27:20.708 --> 27:22.208
So, what you sayin', Blood?

27:24.125 --> 27:27.745
I'm saying... we repossess this gold...

27:29.125 --> 27:32.665
like they about to come repossess
your cash yield convertible now.

27:32.750 --> 27:34.170
[all laughing]

27:36.666 --> 27:41.536
We repossess this gold for every single
black boot that never made it home.

27:42.333 --> 27:46.423
Every brother and sister stolen
from Mother Africa to Jamestown, Virginia

27:46.500 --> 27:48.790
way back in 1619.

27:51.083 --> 27:54.173
We give this gold to our people.

27:55.291 --> 27:58.381
You feel that? You feel it?

28:00.458 --> 28:03.128
-Now, let's bury our gold.
-[Paul] Reparations.

28:03.208 --> 28:05.208
-[glasses clink]
-[Norman] Bloods.

28:05.291 --> 28:06.711
-[gunshot echoes]
-[all]  Bloods.

28:06.791 --> 28:08.671
[distant gunfire]

28:11.000 --> 28:13.960
We went back a few weeks later,
but the area was napalmed,

28:14.041 --> 28:16.331
and we lost all of our landmarks.

28:16.416 --> 28:22.626
But recently, a mudslide has exposed
what might be the C-47's tail,

28:23.291 --> 28:26.381
and satellite pictures
have pinpointed the spot.

28:26.458 --> 28:29.958
Mmm. You're more informed
than your friend here.

28:30.041 --> 28:32.791
Sir, are you in or out?

28:47.500 --> 28:53.420
This is my last offer per kilo,
less my commission.

29:03.833 --> 29:04.883
Tiên said 20.

29:04.958 --> 29:09.208
One cannot carry millions of dollars
through US Customs.

29:09.708 --> 29:13.128
The extra two points will get you
a dummy corporation

29:13.208 --> 29:16.708
and a tax-free offshore account in Macau.

29:17.291 --> 29:21.081
You can then withdraw the funds
from any bank in the world.

29:21.166 --> 29:23.706
How do I know that you two
ain't a con artist team?

29:24.500 --> 29:28.250
As you said, you simply must trust us.

29:28.333 --> 29:32.463
Yeah, well, the extra 2%
comes outta her cut.

29:33.458 --> 29:34.288
That's right.

29:37.333 --> 29:39.503
-I'll cover it.
-Price of doing business.

29:40.416 --> 29:42.666
-So, we good?
-Yeah.

29:44.041 --> 29:45.961
-I'm good.
-Yeah, I'm good.

29:46.708 --> 29:52.128
And, sir, Uncle Sam did no better
than France in Vietnam.

29:53.958 --> 29:57.628
Gentlemen, I look forward
to seeing you again in a few days.

29:57.708 --> 29:59.128
If you will excuse me,

29:59.208 --> 30:02.078
I have a lot of things to do
for all of us.

30:02.916 --> 30:03.996
[in French]

30:05.750 --> 30:06.790
[in English] And, uh...

30:07.291 --> 30:08.421
vive la France.

30:10.041 --> 30:11.711
[in English] This motherfucker, man.

30:12.583 --> 30:13.753
-[door shuts]
-[water running]

30:14.458 --> 30:15.708
[softly] I don't take that.

30:16.791 --> 30:17.881
[water stops running]

30:26.291 --> 30:27.831
What the fuck are you doing here?

30:28.500 --> 30:29.630
I'm worried about you.

30:31.250 --> 30:32.080
Why?

30:33.500 --> 30:36.540
-Well, I found out you were coming here.
-And?

30:37.541 --> 30:39.251
And I came to check on you.

30:41.125 --> 30:44.535
You don't give a flying fuck
about me. [scoffs]

30:44.625 --> 30:47.575
I do. You been acting more crazy
than usual.

30:52.541 --> 30:53.501
Yeah, well...

30:56.041 --> 30:57.461
you consider me checked on.

30:59.208 --> 31:00.578
You're here for the gold.

31:01.375 --> 31:02.205
Don't lie.

31:03.458 --> 31:05.878
You're going after the gold.
I read Otis' emails.

31:07.125 --> 31:11.415
You gotta choose better passwords.
"1-2-3-4"?

31:12.375 --> 31:14.415
[laughs] Come on now, Dad.

31:15.083 --> 31:16.423
What do you want, David?

31:17.000 --> 31:19.580
-An equal share for helping you find it.
-Hell to the naw!

31:19.666 --> 31:23.166
The authorities find out about this,
y'all go back to the crib empty-handed.

31:23.916 --> 31:27.456
So, you just a lil' jive-ass
gangster now, huh?

31:27.541 --> 31:31.791
After everything you've put me through,
I'd say you getting a basement bargain.

31:33.000 --> 31:38.040
You ungrateful lil'...
lil' Black Studies teacher nigga.

31:40.333 --> 31:42.883
You want to tell your Bloods or should I?

31:49.958 --> 31:51.878
[Eddie] You sure know
how to raise 'em, don't you?

31:51.958 --> 31:55.538
What happens if we bum-rush your boy
and throw his ass off that balcony?

31:55.625 --> 31:57.495
Know I'm taking
a couple of you OGs with me.

31:57.583 --> 32:00.083
-Don't ever threaten my son, man.
-Or what?

32:00.166 --> 32:02.286
Or you will nab more trouble
than you know what to do with.

32:02.375 --> 32:03.625
-Oh, come on!
-Come on!

32:03.708 --> 32:05.168
Cool it, God damn it! Cool it!

32:06.958 --> 32:08.538
David, you are not getting a full share.

32:08.625 --> 32:11.035
-You and your daddy can split a share.
-You can forget that.

32:11.125 --> 32:12.325
You take it or leave it.

32:15.458 --> 32:16.628
[sighs]

32:17.833 --> 32:19.543
You see what you made me do, man?

32:20.458 --> 32:21.788
Let me tell you somethin'.

32:22.375 --> 32:25.625
You ain't been nothin'
but an anchor around my neck

32:25.708 --> 32:27.378
since the day you were born.

32:28.416 --> 32:33.076
Yeah, I said it, and I mean it, too.
Take this shit.

32:35.625 --> 32:36.705
God damn it.

32:37.708 --> 32:38.708
[door opens]

32:39.791 --> 32:41.041
[door slams]

32:41.125 --> 32:43.165
David, you're a buck private
in this outfit.

32:43.250 --> 32:47.830
You do what we say when we say it.
No questions asked. Understood?

32:49.375 --> 32:51.325
Overstood, Godfather.

33:00.875 --> 33:04.955
-I have bad feeling about this, Otis.
-I'm gonna be all right.

33:05.541 --> 33:10.831
Gold does strange things to people.
Even old friends. Be safe.

33:22.125 --> 33:24.075
All right. Yeah.

33:25.916 --> 33:27.746
I just hope I don't have to use it.

33:34.500 --> 33:36.210
I'll see you in a bit, all right?

33:38.250 --> 33:40.750
["Ride of the Valkyries" playing]

34:30.791 --> 34:31.920
[inaudible mutter]

35:23.875 --> 35:26.495
-[David] You just gonna stay there?
-Motherfucker, go around.

35:26.583 --> 35:27.883
[chuckling]

35:40.083 --> 35:42.003
-David.
-Yeah?

35:42.083 --> 35:43.633
Why did you come here?

35:46.958 --> 35:48.328
Well, he's my dad.

35:51.291 --> 35:53.041
Feels like my last chance with him.

35:56.333 --> 35:58.883
-He needs counseling.
-I know.

35:59.958 --> 36:02.208
-Talks to himself.
-[sighs]

36:05.291 --> 36:08.001
Your pops was never the same
after we lost Norman.

36:09.750 --> 36:10.750
[Otis] Hmm.

36:11.833 --> 36:15.463
-You know, he calls his name in his sleep.
-I can believe that.

36:17.791 --> 36:20.131
-Who was that guy?
-Norm?

36:21.958 --> 36:25.168
That brother was the best damn soldier
that ever lived.

36:28.708 --> 36:30.458
-[gun cocks]
-[bugs chirring loudly]

36:47.875 --> 36:50.075
[Otis]  Wasn't many brothers
who made squad leader.

36:51.166 --> 36:53.376
The man was using Bloods
for cannon fodder.

36:54.083 --> 36:56.923
White boys who stayed in college,
they'd dodge that shit.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.290
They put our poor black asses
on the front line,

37:00.375 --> 37:02.075
killing us off like flies.

37:04.750 --> 37:06.830
[soldiers speaking Vietnamese in distance]

37:06.916 --> 37:11.456
Stormin' earned his name,
was in all kind of firefights.

37:12.083 --> 37:13.923
Trained us in the way of the jungle.

37:14.000 --> 37:17.500
Made us believe
that we would get home, alive.

37:24.625 --> 37:26.625
[man 1 in Vietnamese]

37:34.375 --> 37:36.035
[soldiers exclaiming]

37:36.125 --> 37:38.245
[man 2 speaking]

37:38.333 --> 37:40.003
[man 1 speaking]

37:46.166 --> 37:48.326
[man 2 speaking]

37:48.416 --> 37:49.666
[man 1 speaking]

37:49.750 --> 37:52.790
[man 3 speaking]

37:53.291 --> 37:54.421
[soldiers scream]

37:55.083 --> 37:56.173
[in English] To your left!

37:56.250 --> 37:59.670
-[Paul] To your left!
-[Norman] To the left! Go, go!

38:07.166 --> 38:08.036
[Norman] Go!

38:08.250 --> 38:09.210
[grunts]

38:21.708 --> 38:23.208
-[Norman] Cease fire!
-[Eddie] Cease fire!

38:23.291 --> 38:25.001
-[Paul] Cease fire!
-Cease fire!

38:25.583 --> 38:27.463
-[Otis] Everybody all right?
-[Melvin] Yeah.

38:27.541 --> 38:29.251
-[Paul] Good right here.
-[Eddie] Good, good.

38:32.291 --> 38:33.751
War is about money.

38:36.250 --> 38:37.580
Money is about war.

38:38.333 --> 38:40.543
Every time I walk out my front door,

38:41.083 --> 38:43.833
I see cops patrolling my neighborhood
like it's some police state.

38:43.916 --> 38:47.286
I can feel just how much I ain't worth.

38:50.375 --> 38:52.745
-[slide projector clicks]
-[Otis]  Gave us something to believe in.

38:53.333 --> 38:55.383
A direction, a purpose.

38:56.541 --> 38:59.751
He taught us about black history
when it wasn't really popular back then.

39:01.041 --> 39:04.541
Schooled us about drinking that
anti-commie Kool-Aid they was selling.

39:05.333 --> 39:08.253
Yeah, he was our Malcolm and our Martin.

39:09.291 --> 39:11.921
Norm had a way of keeping us
from going off.

39:12.750 --> 39:14.000
He wasn't no Tom.

39:15.250 --> 39:18.170
He was a bad mother, shut your mouth.

39:18.250 --> 39:19.380
[chuckles]

39:20.166 --> 39:21.166
Like Ali.

39:27.291 --> 39:32.541
[woman over radio]  This is the voice
of Vietnam, broadcasting from Hanoi,

39:32.625 --> 39:37.035
capital of the Democratic Republic
of Vietnam.

39:41.333 --> 39:42.673
Black GI,

39:43.625 --> 39:49.575
in Memphis, Tennessee, a white man
assassinate Dr. Martin Luther King...

39:50.708 --> 39:53.878
who heroically opposed the cruel

39:53.958 --> 39:57.458
-racial discrimination in the USA.
-[single gunshot]

39:58.166 --> 40:02.786
Dr. King also opposed
the US war in Vietnam.

40:04.541 --> 40:10.291
Black GI, your government
sent 600,000 troops

40:10.375 --> 40:11.915
to crush the rebellion.

40:12.541 --> 40:19.501
Your soul sister and soul brothers
are enraged in over 122 cities.

40:20.125 --> 40:27.075
They kill them while you fight against us,
so far away from where you are needed.

40:29.250 --> 40:33.920
Black GI, the South Vietnamese people
are resolute

40:34.000 --> 40:37.040
against these fascist acts against Negroes

40:37.541 --> 40:40.251
who struggle for civil rights and freedom.

40:42.750 --> 40:47.920
Negroes are only 11% of the US population,

40:48.500 --> 40:52.210
but among troops here in Vietnam,
you are 32%.

40:54.625 --> 40:59.325
Black GI, is it fair to serve more
than the white Americans

40:59.416 --> 41:00.666
that sent you here?

41:01.166 --> 41:06.416
Nothing is more confuse
than to be ordered into a war to die

41:06.916 --> 41:12.036
or to be maimed for life without
the faintest idea of what's going on.

41:13.416 --> 41:15.786
I dedicate this next record

41:15.875 --> 41:19.625
to the soul brothers
of the 1st Infantry Divisions.

41:20.291 --> 41:24.921
Big Red One, 2nd Battalion,
136th Regiment.

41:25.708 --> 41:27.458
Have a good day, gentlemen.

41:31.416 --> 41:32.416
Be safe.

41:33.625 --> 41:36.705
-Goddamn bullshit.
-Got the wrong motherfucking enemy!

41:36.791 --> 41:39.131
Yeah, goddamn white man gone too far.

41:39.208 --> 41:42.498
-The Bible says an eye for an eye.
-And a tooth for a tooth.

41:42.583 --> 41:44.253
We need to kill some crackers.

41:44.333 --> 41:47.333
Our brothers and sisters
are burnin' shit down back home, Norm.

41:48.458 --> 41:51.538
I love you, man, but you're wrong.
Dead wrong.

41:51.625 --> 41:56.325
You're talking about Dr. King.
You're talking about a man of peace.

41:56.916 --> 41:58.786
And that's what got Dr. King killed.

41:59.291 --> 42:03.041
I'm as mad as everybody.
All us Bloods got a right to be, but...

42:05.208 --> 42:06.378
we Bloods.

42:07.875 --> 42:11.415
Won't let nobody use our rage against us.
We control our rage.

42:12.416 --> 42:16.036
Now, what y'all are trying to do right now
ain't changing shit.

42:17.458 --> 42:19.998
So, stand down. That's an order.

42:20.083 --> 42:22.173
Nah. Fuck an order, Norm!

42:25.666 --> 42:27.416
You're gonna have to kill me first.

42:29.958 --> 42:31.248
Blood on Blood.

43:29.333 --> 43:30.583
[screams]

43:31.791 --> 43:33.211
[all screaming]

43:36.583 --> 43:40.463
[Otis]  And let me tell you, out of all
of us, your pops was closest to him.

43:40.958 --> 43:43.078
Believed in Norman like a religion.

43:43.583 --> 43:46.173
I don't think he believed
in anything since.

43:47.916 --> 43:51.376
[Vinh] Floating market.
You brothers want anything?

43:51.458 --> 43:52.748
[Eddie] Is there some barbecue up in here?

43:52.833 --> 43:54.293
[Melvin] I might get a couple of things.

43:54.375 --> 43:55.955
[Vinh speaking Vietnamese]

43:57.666 --> 43:59.786
[Eddie in English] What's that?
You got bananas?

43:59.875 --> 44:02.125
[speaking Vietnamese]

44:02.208 --> 44:04.628
-Whoa!
-Hey, who wants a cold one?

44:04.708 --> 44:05.748
[overlapping chatter]

44:05.833 --> 44:07.793
-Six pack.
-[Paul] Bring 'em on up.

44:07.875 --> 44:09.245
Hey, don't let her get on.

44:11.125 --> 44:11.955
That's good.

44:12.041 --> 44:13.001
Hey!

44:13.416 --> 44:14.706
-Oranges?
-[Eddie] Get your beer here.

44:14.791 --> 44:16.211
-[Vinh] This is good.
-[Eddie] Here you go.

44:16.291 --> 44:19.831
You're gonna cut it open? No, I'm good.
So, how you eat it?

44:21.166 --> 44:22.206
It tastes like chicken.

44:22.291 --> 44:25.131
That probably don't taste like chicken.
That's race-related.

44:25.208 --> 44:27.878
[in Vietnamese]

44:29.916 --> 44:30.956
