♪ Tell me what's going on ♪

01:54:54.500 --> 01:54:59.790
♪ I'll tell you what's going on, whoo ♪

01:54:59.875 --> 01:55:01.785
♪ Right on, baby
Right on ♪

01:55:02.416 --> 01:55:04.286
[scatting]

01:55:06.625 --> 01:55:07.455
♪ Right on ♪

01:55:10.000 --> 01:55:13.170
Their mind's weak.
They got no intestinal fortitude.

01:55:15.375 --> 01:55:18.325
Ain't as strong as Paul. No, no, sir.

01:55:18.833 --> 01:55:21.543
Ain't got the guts Paul got.
It ain't their fault.

01:55:23.166 --> 01:55:26.626
They was born weak. Otis and his ho.

01:55:27.958 --> 01:55:32.208
Car thieves, guttersnipes,
chain snatchers.

01:55:34.083 --> 01:55:38.793
They ain't snatching... my gold bars.

01:55:40.208 --> 01:55:42.578
Not Paul. No, sir.

01:55:43.833 --> 01:55:45.673
I ain't getting fucked again.

01:55:45.750 --> 01:55:48.750
Trying to fuck me
with that salt in the Vaseline.

01:55:52.333 --> 01:55:55.003
Not Paul. Not this time.

01:55:57.041 --> 01:55:57.881
No.

01:55:59.291 --> 01:56:04.711
Them son of bitches. Son of bitches.
Son of...

01:56:06.541 --> 01:56:08.001
Turned my own son against me.

01:56:14.208 --> 01:56:15.378
My own blood.

01:56:16.500 --> 01:56:17.580
God damn.

01:56:20.333 --> 01:56:21.253
Well...

01:56:23.666 --> 01:56:25.576
we gonna see who's standing in the end.

01:56:26.916 --> 01:56:31.956
I don't care what the VA say.
VA don't know shit from Shinola.

01:56:32.041 --> 01:56:36.381
Worst fucking doctors in the world.
Malignancy? Shit.

01:56:39.375 --> 01:56:41.285
You made me malignant.

01:56:43.750 --> 01:56:45.630
This fucking place here...

01:56:50.166 --> 01:56:55.076
bathed me in that lymphoma
Agent Orange herbicidal stew.

01:56:55.166 --> 01:56:57.576
Those army bastards,
they scorched the earth with it.

01:56:57.666 --> 01:56:59.916
Sprayed that shit in the air
and the water,

01:57:00.000 --> 01:57:04.790
my bloodstream, my cells,
my DNA, and my motherfucking soul!

01:57:07.333 --> 01:57:08.713
But I ain't dying...

01:57:09.791 --> 01:57:10.921
from that shit.

01:57:13.000 --> 01:57:14.210
You will not...

01:57:15.458 --> 01:57:16.748
kill Paul.

01:57:17.833 --> 01:57:18.923
You hear me?

01:57:24.250 --> 01:57:25.290
Hear me.

01:57:28.833 --> 01:57:32.083
You will not kill Paul.

01:57:34.333 --> 01:57:36.963
And the US government
will not take me out.

01:57:39.958 --> 01:57:41.418
I will choose

01:57:42.458 --> 01:57:43.378
when...

01:57:45.291 --> 01:57:47.541
and how I die.

01:57:48.958 --> 01:57:50.078
You dig?

01:57:51.166 --> 01:57:54.626
You couldn't kill me then,
with three tours,

01:57:55.291 --> 01:57:58.881
you sure in the fuck can't kill me now.

01:58:00.833 --> 01:58:01.833
Right on?

01:58:05.708 --> 01:58:06.828
Right on.

01:58:12.916 --> 01:58:14.166
Right on.

01:58:19.000 --> 01:58:20.920
Right on.

01:58:34.208 --> 01:58:36.628
[Otis breathing heavily]

01:58:42.541 --> 01:58:45.501
-I know that thing is throbbing like hell.
-Yeah.

01:58:46.750 --> 01:58:47.880
[pills rattling]

01:58:51.750 --> 01:58:52.670
Thanks.

01:58:53.416 --> 01:58:56.246
Don't thank me. Thank your Uncle Meli-Mel.

01:58:57.833 --> 01:58:58.963
You OGs.

01:59:06.833 --> 01:59:09.923
Hedy, he's running a fever.
I think that wound is infected.

01:59:23.833 --> 01:59:24.963
Look after him.

01:59:44.625 --> 01:59:46.165
[screaming and grunting]

01:59:47.625 --> 01:59:49.455
Get off me! Get off!

01:59:49.541 --> 01:59:51.541
[grunting]

01:59:53.291 --> 01:59:54.631
Get off!

02:00:00.083 --> 02:00:01.333
[in Vietnamese]

02:00:03.666 --> 02:00:04.876
[grunts]

02:00:14.625 --> 02:00:17.035
[Hedy] What's the issue
between you and your father?

02:00:21.625 --> 02:00:22.575
Jacklyn.

02:00:24.375 --> 02:00:25.575
Who is she?

02:00:30.875 --> 02:00:31.955
My mother.

02:00:35.333 --> 02:00:36.463
My mom...

02:00:39.750 --> 02:00:43.130
She had a very difficult delivery.

02:00:52.333 --> 02:00:53.883
And she didn't survive?

02:01:10.041 --> 02:01:11.501
My apology.

02:01:14.333 --> 02:01:18.173
I'm intruding. It's none of my business.

02:01:19.666 --> 02:01:20.916
My father...

02:01:23.958 --> 02:01:25.628
he loved her more than me.

02:01:28.083 --> 02:01:29.793
Never let me forget that either.

02:01:34.791 --> 02:01:37.501
He has hated me since the day I was born.

02:01:38.875 --> 02:01:40.325
[voice breaks] All my fault.

02:01:46.750 --> 02:01:49.750
[sniffles]
I should've died instead of my mother.

02:02:05.875 --> 02:02:09.035
[grunts] Goddamn snakebite. Come on.

02:02:10.875 --> 02:02:13.375
[yells] Mother... Fuck you!

02:02:13.916 --> 02:02:15.416
[screaming]

02:02:15.916 --> 02:02:16.786
Fuck!

02:02:19.083 --> 02:02:20.213
[groans]

02:02:21.958 --> 02:02:23.128
[grunts]

02:02:29.666 --> 02:02:30.706
[laughs]

02:02:31.208 --> 02:02:32.248
Oof.

02:02:33.125 --> 02:02:37.825
God, you're a trickster.
Oh, God. You're a trickster.

02:02:39.250 --> 02:02:42.420
[laughing] Come to Papa.

02:02:50.208 --> 02:02:51.288
[grunting softly]

02:03:08.083 --> 02:03:09.213
[groans]

02:03:22.708 --> 02:03:23.878
[exhales heavily]

02:03:36.291 --> 02:03:38.461
Oh, f-- [chuckles]

02:03:43.750 --> 02:03:46.670
You got it, Norm. All for you, baby.

02:03:48.125 --> 02:03:49.415
[laughing]

02:03:53.750 --> 02:03:55.000
Life is a bitch!

02:04:00.083 --> 02:04:03.253
If I gotta go out, I gotta go out
like a man, Blood.

02:04:04.666 --> 02:04:07.126
-Morals and ethics.
-Hmm.

02:04:07.208 --> 02:04:09.128
Sounds like Stormin' Norman.

02:04:11.958 --> 02:04:13.828
You know,
I keep hearing his voice in my head,

02:04:13.916 --> 02:04:16.036
telling me to do right,
just to get it right.

02:04:17.041 --> 02:04:17.921
[sighs]

02:04:19.375 --> 02:04:22.125
Stormin' had this whole living thing
figured out.

02:04:23.666 --> 02:04:26.206
We are not gonna die in Nam.

02:04:30.750 --> 02:04:32.290
Come on, let's battle, Blood.

02:04:47.708 --> 02:04:48.538
[both] Bloods.

02:04:48.625 --> 02:04:51.995
I was asleep. Man, I was fast asleep,
knocked out, man.

02:04:52.750 --> 02:04:54.250
God poked and woke me.

02:04:55.791 --> 02:04:59.131
I said, "God... God, why you
waking my black ass up?"

02:04:59.583 --> 02:05:04.253
God said to me,
"Paul, fuck them motherfuckers.

02:05:04.666 --> 02:05:06.166
Keep on keeping on."

02:05:08.000 --> 02:05:11.330
I said to God, "God, do what now?"

02:05:12.375 --> 02:05:14.415
God raised His voice, didn't yell,

02:05:14.500 --> 02:05:18.210
but put some bass
in that heavenly voice, said to me,

02:05:19.875 --> 02:05:22.995
"Fuck them motherfuckers, Paul.
They don't know shit.

02:05:23.500 --> 02:05:26.040
Do your thing. Show you're right."

02:05:47.166 --> 02:05:48.576
What you doing here, bruh?

02:05:50.541 --> 02:05:52.211
I've been wanting to talk to you.

02:05:53.666 --> 02:05:54.786
About what?

02:05:56.083 --> 02:05:57.133
You know.

02:06:00.875 --> 02:06:01.825
Go away, man.

02:06:03.416 --> 02:06:04.286
Please?

02:06:06.000 --> 02:06:09.210
No, no, come on now.
Come on now. Come on now.

02:06:10.583 --> 02:06:12.213
That I can't do, Paul.

02:06:17.916 --> 02:06:19.456
Gonna have to come clean.

02:06:20.958 --> 02:06:23.828
[gunshots echoing]

02:06:32.958 --> 02:06:35.168
[gunshots continue in distance]

02:07:09.750 --> 02:07:11.750
-[Paul exclaims]
-[soldier screams]

02:07:11.833 --> 02:07:13.293
[Paul] Hey, Norm! Norm!

02:07:19.000 --> 02:07:19.830
Hey.

02:07:23.500 --> 02:07:25.420
[groans softly]

02:07:51.250 --> 02:07:52.250
There it is.

02:08:08.375 --> 02:08:09.285
[Paul grunts]

02:08:15.333 --> 02:08:17.083
It was an accident.

02:08:20.958 --> 02:08:22.498
Ain't no thing, Blood.

02:08:24.833 --> 02:08:25.923
Accident.

02:08:29.666 --> 02:08:30.996
I forgive you.

02:08:33.041 --> 02:08:34.131
You hear that?

02:08:36.666 --> 02:08:37.746
I forgive you.

02:08:39.833 --> 02:08:41.003
Ain't no thing, Blood.

02:08:44.041 --> 02:08:45.171
Come on now.

02:08:46.750 --> 02:08:49.080
Come on, Paul. Come on, Blood.

02:08:52.750 --> 02:08:54.040
I forgive you.

02:08:57.791 --> 02:08:59.081
God is love.

02:09:00.833 --> 02:09:02.133
Love is God.

02:09:07.833 --> 02:09:10.383
Come on. Hey, you got me now.

02:09:12.250 --> 02:09:13.460
[Paul crying]

02:09:13.541 --> 02:09:16.791
You got me good. Ain't no thing.

02:09:18.041 --> 02:09:19.501
[Paul sobbing loudly]

02:09:26.208 --> 02:09:28.208
I'm sorr... [sobbing]

02:09:32.000 --> 02:09:34.830
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

02:09:36.875 --> 02:09:38.205
I know you, Blood.

02:09:40.500 --> 02:09:41.960
I died for you, Blood.

02:09:46.041 --> 02:09:49.211
[Quân] Keep digging. You're outnumbered.

02:09:51.166 --> 02:09:53.246
We're always outnumbered.

02:09:54.250 --> 02:09:55.330
Where's gold?

02:09:55.416 --> 02:09:57.286
Stormin' Norman took it, man.

02:09:59.458 --> 02:10:00.538
It was his.

02:10:00.958 --> 02:10:02.248
Who's Stormin' Norman?

02:10:03.416 --> 02:10:05.746
One bad black motherfucker.

02:10:06.916 --> 02:10:08.786
-Where's all the GI?
-[Paul grunts]

02:10:09.583 --> 02:10:12.003
No, I will never tell.

02:10:12.583 --> 02:10:17.423
See, we're Bloods. We got a bond.

02:10:18.791 --> 02:10:23.381
We fought... in a immoral war
that wasn't ours,

02:10:23.458 --> 02:10:27.288
for rights... for rights we didn't have.

02:10:29.250 --> 02:10:30.330
They're my brothers.

02:10:30.416 --> 02:10:32.286
You killed my brother.

02:10:35.041 --> 02:10:35.961
I did.

02:10:38.916 --> 02:10:43.246
♪ Don't go and talk about my father ♪

02:10:43.750 --> 02:10:48.210
♪ God is my friend
Jesus is my friend ♪

02:10:49.583 --> 02:10:53.673
♪ He made this world for us to live in ♪

02:10:55.166 --> 02:10:58.416
♪ And gave us everything ♪

02:10:59.000 --> 02:11:01.580
♪ All He asks of us ♪

02:11:03.666 --> 02:11:08.126
♪ Is we give each other love ♪

02:11:10.458 --> 02:11:12.958
-My brother, Marvin.
-You're drunk.

02:11:13.041 --> 02:11:15.791
-I ain't never been more sober in my life.
-Dig!

02:11:17.958 --> 02:11:20.168
Okay, it's deep enough, man.

02:11:20.791 --> 02:11:21.671
Okay...

02:11:22.750 --> 02:11:23.710
dig.

02:11:23.791 --> 02:11:25.581
[grunting]

02:11:26.333 --> 02:11:29.043
♪ Don't go and talk about my father... ♪

02:11:29.125 --> 02:11:30.125
Faster!

02:11:30.958 --> 02:11:32.128
♪ God... ♪

02:11:32.208 --> 02:11:33.038
[Quân] Faster!

02:11:33.125 --> 02:11:35.415
♪ ...Is my friend
Jesus is my friend ♪

02:11:35.500 --> 02:11:36.540
[Quân] Faster!

02:11:36.625 --> 02:11:37.665
♪ He loves us ♪

02:11:38.291 --> 02:11:39.131
Faster.

02:11:39.208 --> 02:11:41.958
♪ Whether or not we know it ♪

02:11:44.000 --> 02:11:49.630
♪ And He'll forgive us all our sins ♪

02:12:05.791 --> 02:12:07.041
[Melvin] You all right up there?

02:12:07.125 --> 02:12:08.575
-Keep your eyes open.
-On it.

02:12:08.666 --> 02:12:09.956
[Melvin] Kool and the Gang.

02:12:13.416 --> 02:12:16.956
After you've been in a war,
you understand it really never ends.

02:12:19.750 --> 02:12:24.130
Whether it's in your mind or in reality.
There are just degrees.

02:12:24.208 --> 02:12:25.748
Tell me about it.

02:12:30.166 --> 02:12:34.376
If I happen to die, send my share here.

02:12:42.125 --> 02:12:44.205
One of you two should have this.

02:12:44.291 --> 02:12:45.501
No. I don't want it.

02:12:45.583 --> 02:12:47.213
I ain't fired a gun in my life.

02:12:47.291 --> 02:12:50.081
I shoot, I'd probably miss by a mile,
especially with my leg.

02:12:54.166 --> 02:12:56.496
My father? You seen him?

02:12:57.166 --> 02:12:58.826
[Melvin] My hunch is Desroche is with him.

02:12:58.916 --> 02:13:00.956
-[Hedy] Who?
-One of your countrymen.

02:13:01.583 --> 02:13:04.333
He set up our deal,
probably gave us the old flimflam.

02:13:04.416 --> 02:13:06.166
Perhaps I could appeal to him.

02:13:06.666 --> 02:13:07.916
[Melvin] Worth a try.

02:13:09.041 --> 02:13:10.291
Are you ready for this?

02:13:10.875 --> 02:13:13.075
Blood, this ain't my first time in Nam.

02:13:31.583 --> 02:13:33.963
Well, if we live, you'll teach me that.
[chuckles]

02:13:34.041 --> 02:13:35.251
[Melvin] We're all gonna live.

02:13:35.833 --> 02:13:41.633
And maybe someday if I come to Paris,
you can show me the "Champs-Eleesees."

02:13:42.375 --> 02:13:43.575
[Hedy] The what?

02:13:43.666 --> 02:13:46.246
You know, the "Champs-Eleesees"?
That big thing y'all got.

02:13:46.333 --> 02:13:49.083
[laughs] The Champs-Élysées.

02:13:50.291 --> 02:13:51.751
-[Melvin] Bet?
-Bet.

02:13:54.083 --> 02:13:56.293
-Remember the plan.
-[Hedy continues laughing]

02:13:56.375 --> 02:13:57.495
Yes, sir.

02:14:03.291 --> 02:14:04.751
[vehicles approaching]

02:14:16.333 --> 02:14:18.133
[men chattering indistinctly]

02:14:38.125 --> 02:14:39.995
Who is your pretty companion?

02:14:41.250 --> 02:14:43.460
[in French]

02:14:43.541 --> 02:14:44.421
[Desroche] Ah.

02:15:03.625 --> 02:15:04.875
[in English] What'd he just say?

02:15:05.791 --> 02:15:08.381
That the green
is more important than black.

02:15:08.458 --> 02:15:10.128
[in French]

02:15:10.208 --> 02:15:11.878
[in English] He asks for Norman's share.

02:15:13.083 --> 02:15:15.423
[sighs] I don't know.

02:15:17.541 --> 02:15:20.291
Norman is pretty particular
about what he shares.

02:15:23.166 --> 02:15:25.286
-May I ask you a question?
-Yes.

02:15:27.666 --> 02:15:30.036
Was Tiên in on all this?

02:15:31.125 --> 02:15:34.825
Tiên is a very smart woman,
but she doesn't have the appetite

02:15:34.916 --> 02:15:38.376
for a venture like this.
She knows nothing about this.

02:15:39.333 --> 02:15:42.003
She is as innocent as you are ignorant.

02:15:45.625 --> 02:15:47.125
Well, take the gold and...

02:15:50.083 --> 02:15:51.333
leave in peace.

02:15:52.500 --> 02:15:53.380
Go with God.

02:15:54.333 --> 02:15:56.503
We just want what we came for.

02:15:56.583 --> 02:15:57.423
Good.

02:16:26.750 --> 02:16:27.960
[Quân] You bastards!

02:16:32.500 --> 02:16:34.129
[men yelling in Vietnamese]

02:16:44.790 --> 02:16:46.290
[groans]

02:16:52.665 --> 02:16:54.075
[Desroche] Go, go, go!

02:16:59.165 --> 02:17:00.626
[grunting]

02:17:02.083 --> 02:17:03.293
[swears in French]

02:17:05.665 --> 02:17:06.495
[groans]

02:17:19.833 --> 02:17:21.293
[Desroche grunting]

02:17:24.290 --> 02:17:26.460
[groaning]

02:17:28.958 --> 02:17:30.878
[groans loudly]

02:17:36.540 --> 02:17:38.751
-[Vinh] I can't feel a thing.
-Fuck.

02:17:39.833 --> 02:17:42.253
Straight through. Through and through.

02:17:42.333 --> 02:17:44.423
-You'll survive, buddy.
-[Vinh] Be safe.

02:17:44.500 --> 02:17:45.709
[gun firing]

02:17:59.833 --> 02:18:01.423
[groans]

02:18:12.375 --> 02:18:13.285
Grenade!

02:18:16.415 --> 02:18:18.415
No! [groaning]

02:18:23.790 --> 02:18:25.540
[continues groaning]

02:18:29.040 --> 02:18:30.921
[Desroche] Your Bloods are all dead.

02:18:32.415 --> 02:18:33.995
There is no one left.

02:18:40.125 --> 02:18:41.455
[in French]

02:18:42.708 --> 02:18:43.958
[in English] Where is the gold?

02:18:46.625 --> 02:18:51.625
Five Bloods don't die, we multiply.

02:18:54.750 --> 02:18:55.920
Allow me.

02:18:57.290 --> 02:18:58.421
[Desroche groans and thuds]

02:19:06.583 --> 02:19:07.713
[Otis laughing]

02:19:09.750 --> 02:19:13.500
Madness! Madness!

02:19:13.583 --> 02:19:15.083
[continues laughing]

02:19:24.708 --> 02:19:26.788
[David] Godfather, you'll be all right.

02:19:29.290 --> 02:19:30.421
[Otis laughing]

02:19:38.000 --> 02:19:40.000
[solemn instrumental music plays]

02:19:43.665 --> 02:19:44.876
[Paul]  Dear David.

02:19:46.625 --> 02:19:47.785
Son...

02:19:50.416 --> 02:19:53.746
if you're reading this,
you know I've met my maker.

02:20:04.916 --> 02:20:08.126
I gave this letter to... my main man,

02:20:10.041 --> 02:20:13.251
your godfather, Otis,

02:20:13.875 --> 02:20:15.535
when we landed back in Nam.

02:20:17.875 --> 02:20:23.825
I came back to confront the demons
that haunted me and tortured you.

02:20:25.875 --> 02:20:27.955
I made you feel like you weren't loved.

02:20:32.041 --> 02:20:38.001
Our brother Stormin' Norman always
commanded us Bloods, love one another.

02:20:40.500 --> 02:20:42.170
In that way, I failed you, man.

02:20:44.291 --> 02:20:46.001
All I can say to you is...

02:20:49.458 --> 02:20:52.038
I'm sorry I put you through holy hell.

02:20:56.916 --> 02:20:58.166
Believe me...

02:20:58.791 --> 02:20:59.961
This just came.

02:21:02.000 --> 02:21:03.380
[Paul]  ...it wasn't your fault.

02:21:06.208 --> 02:21:10.668
There are things about me that you
will never know or understand, David.

02:21:20.000 --> 02:21:21.920
I wish I could turn back
the hands of time...

02:21:33.583 --> 02:21:34.463
I can't.

02:21:40.583 --> 02:21:41.503
Nobody can.

02:21:46.625 --> 02:21:48.625
-[man] Mic check!
-[all] Mic check!

02:21:48.708 --> 02:21:50.328
-[man] Mic check!
-[all] Mic check!

02:21:50.416 --> 02:21:52.206
I got something I gotta share with y'all.

02:21:52.291 --> 02:21:54.921
We just received a check
from our soldier Eddie

02:21:55.000 --> 02:21:56.880
for two million dollars!

02:21:56.958 --> 02:21:58.628
[all cheering]

02:22:00.083 --> 02:22:02.083
-Mic check!
-[all] Mic check!

02:22:02.166 --> 02:22:04.496
-Mic check!
-[all] Mic check!

02:22:04.583 --> 02:22:07.043
